entry.title: [Android] Fix race condition when flag test overrides are unset
entry.content:
When the flag test values are unset while checking a test value, we

may get:



java.lang.NullPointerException: Attempt to read from field

'java.util.Map org.chromium.base.FeatureList$TestValues.mFeatureFlags'

on a null object reference



This works around the issue by storing the Map in a local variable

instead of getting it again from the static field. The better fix is

to lock down flag state and stop resetting it (crbug.com/1434471), but

it requires much more work to change existing tests that rely on it.

entry.title: [css-anchor-position] Speculative @try styling
entry.content:
Any normal style recalc (that's not triggered by layout) does

currently not include any declaration from @try rules.

Such declarations appear only via UpdateStyleForPositionFallback,

which is triggered by OOF layout.



This is problematic, because any normal style recalc that happens

*after* UpdateStyleForPositionFallback has taken place, will never

include any @try styles, and therefore always produce an

invalidation diff representing whatever the chosen @try style

provided. In practice, this means a style mutation that should

only invalidate paint (e.g. a opacity change) will always invalidate

layout as well.



To fix this, this CL introduces speculative @try styling, where

the most recently used @try declarations ("try set") is stored

on the target Element, and any style resolution (regardless of its

source) will include that set in its cascade. If we invalidated

layout with that style resolution, then we'll check if our

speculation was correct, and update the style if it wasn't.

If we did *not* invalidate layout with that style resolution,

then layout hasn't changed, and our @try choice isn't going to

change either (i.e. our speculation was correct).



Note that the case of an element losing its OOF status must

be explicitly handled, because we won't enter OOF layout

to check the correctess of our speculation in that case.

(See StyleCascade::TreatAsRevertLayer).

entry.title: PA: Do not enable partition_alloc on MSVC cl.exe.
entry.content:
We previously enforced MSVC cl.exe should build PA's allocator, PA's

allocator_shim, etc...



This is good... but there are currently no ways to configure GN not to

build them. Indeed there are no "use_partition_alloc_default" argument

defined.



Adding a new GN build argument "use_partition_alloc_default" would be

an option. However, this would break dependants, because it would

initially appear as undefined for them. We could use something like

"dawn_overrides_with_default.gni" to avoid problems. It is probably a

good thing to do. I abandoned the idea, because I would like not mixing

two kind of CLs.



Anyway, if we only support gcc or clang, we don't need a GN argument, we

can directly disable them, the same way we do with NaCl.

entry.title: [ios] Fix layout issue after undoing a "close all tabs" operation
entry.content:
To fix a visual glitch when undoing the "close all tabs" operation

restore both active and inactive tabs (the restoration happening in

two steps), the tiles are inserted with a size of 0.



With the current implementation of the undo (which save the session

when closing the tabs and restore the session to perform the undo),

some tabs will perform a navigation as part of the restoration. The

navigation will eventually result in a relayout (e.g. when the tab

title changes) which will set the correct dimension on the tiles.



If no navigation happens as part of the session restoration (e.g. if

the active tab is pinned, and there are no active unpinned tabs) or

if the navigation is too slow (e.g. slow network), then the tab grid

will appear empty. If the user tap "done" at this point, the UI will

try to animate a tab of size 0, leading to a CHECK failure in the

method -scaleTabViews.



To fix this, invalidate the layout after the whole undo operation is

complete, forcing the correct dimension to be computed for the tiles.



This is a reland of https://crrev.com/c/5040433 which was reverted

by mistake in https://crrev.com/c/5033771 probably during a rebase.



Fixed: 1427258

entry.content:
The following test:

BookmarksAccountStoragePromoTestCase/testOnlyAccountModelNotShownOnSignout

has been flaky since its creation and this is due to how menu items used

to work on older iOS version.

coexist simultaneously, but only one of them will be visible.

- So, to fix this, the test's conditions were modified to specifically

look only for visible items, which fixes the flake.

entry.title: RegisterPublisher when controller is ready for Chrome apps in Lacros.
entry.content:
When the AppStorage is enabled, the apps could be published and

launched, before the lacros mojom controller is ready. Move the

publisher register(RegisterPublisher) in

StandaloneBrowserExtensionApps to RegisterAppController, when the

lacros mojom controller is ready. So we can show the icon spinner if

the mojom controller is not ready. And once the controller is ready,

the saved app launch info can be sent to the lacros side to launch the

app.



The change in StandaloneBrowserExtensionApps is also consistent with

WebAppsCrosapi.

entry.title: [DevTools] Ensure info passed to `AutofillHandler` contains the
entry.content:
autofilled values



The `AutofillHandler` for DevTools, which is called via

`NotifyObservers()`, is interested in the filled fields' values. These

values are non-empty only for the `result` variable, and not for the

`form` variable (because `result.fields` and not `form.fields` are

passed to `FillFieldWithValue()`).



This CL ensures that the notified observers receive `FormFieldData`

which contains the freshly autofilled values by passing the `result`

variable's fields instead of the `form` variable's fields.

> to inherit the gn config from neon_2_sse.

> Specifically the file neon_check.h has the include:

> #include "NEON_2_SSE.h"

> "-Wno-gnu-inline-cpp-without-extern." Disabling this is already

> in tflite_flags, but it really belongs in neon2 as that is the

> place with the issue.

> The fix for 1&2 is only done for the standalone target as we don't

> want to add public configs to targets that disable compiler warnings.

entry.title: [Password generation] Fix showing update password message twice when updating the generated password with empty username
entry.content:
This bug fix is only related to the very specific user flow: the user

has accepted the generated password in the form with empty username

while having already saved credential with empty username for this web

site.



Current flow: we show the update password message even before filling

the password into the form (here

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:components/password_manager/core/browser/password_generation_manager.cc;l=333;bpv=0;bpt=1).

If the user clicks "Update", the generation manager pre-saves the

password. Then after the user submits the form, the second update

password message comes from PasswordManager::OnLoginSuccessful (here

https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:components/password_manager/core/browser/password_manager.cc;l=1150;drc=719c18366c0226fa751f38693b00f822d1b7ea9b?q=password_manager.cc).



Solution: PasswordManager::ShouldPromptUserToSavePassword should return

false. For this to fulfill, the changes into PasswordSaveManager are

being introduced, so that it takes into account the pre-saved password

when calculating PendingCredentialsState.



Update.

entry.title: Implement Identifier Literal type for css math
entry.content:
With introduction of *progress() functions:

https://drafts.csswg.org/css-values-5/#media-progress-func

and

https://drafts.csswg.org/css-values-5/#container-progress-func

there is a need to save the identifier argument to these functions,

as later we need to update the computed value based on this identifier,

whether it's a media name or container name.



This is not possible, as the only literal terminator now is a number.

So, in order to be able to save it, string literal type is introduced.



Also, it can be useful to determine which container the container unit

refers to (e.g., cqi():

https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/7858
